nodes.description: The Name the actor is generally referred to as.  An entry can have multiple name values with different name types - e.g. a person may have a Primary name they are referred to as and an Alternative name.
nodes.name: Name

nodes.description: The type of Name described via the previous "Name value" attribute - e.g. Primary, Official, Alternative. Controlled by a Thesaurus (uses the main site Thesaurus for Name types). An entry can have multiple name values with different name types - e.g. a person may have a Primary name they are referred to as and an Alternative name.
nodes.name: Name type

nodes.description: The date that this resource was initially created.
nodes.name: Resource created at

nodes.description: The date that this resource was modified, if it is later modified from its initial form (e.g. if a person leaves an institution to work elsewhere).
nodes.name: Resource last modified at

nodes.description: A text description of the location of this actor - for institutions this might be the address of the institution, or for people this might be where they are based professionally (not personal addresses). This does not need to be extremely detailed (or even included at all) if details cannot be provided or if an actor does not want to provide them.
nodes.name: Address

nodes.description: The Type of Actor which this resource represents - e.g. a member of the MAEASaM team (a type of person), or a Museum (a type of institution). Controlled by a hierarchical Thesaurus (only certain values valid)
nodes.name: Actor type
